{{unreferenced|date=May 2014}} {{Expand French|Société asiatique|date=July 2015}} The '''Société Asiatique''' is a [[France|French]] [[learned society]] dedicated to the study of [[Asia]]. It was founded in 1822 with the mission of developing and diffusing knowledge of Asia. Its boundaries of geographic interest are broad, ranging from the [[Maghreb]] to the [[Far East]]. The society publishes the ''[[Journal asiatique]]''. At present the society has about 700 members in France and abroad; its library contains over 90,000 volumes.
== History == The establishment of the society was confirmed by royal ordinance on April 15, 1829. Antoine-Isaac Silvestre de Sacy was the first president.
